Author: Copilot

`_resolve_prog()` always derives `prog` from `sys.argv[0]`, which means programmatic calls like `main([...])` (used throughout the test suite) will render help/errors/version with the caller’s executable name (e.g., `pytest`) rather than `cfafi`/`cultureflare`. It also makes `python -m cfafi ...` likely show `__main__.py` as the program name. Consider treating `argv is not None` as a signal to use a stable canonical prog (e.g., `cultureflare`), and/or special-casing `__main__.py` to return `cultureflare`/`cfafi` instead of the module filename.

